data.chText: 贸易的；商业的
data.enText: connected with the buying and selling of goods and services

data.chText: 城市的商业中心
data.enText: the commercial heart of the city

data.chText: 商用车辆
data.enText: a commercial vehicle (= one that is used for carrying goods or passengers who pay)

data.chText: 市面上的婴儿食品
data.enText: commercial baby foods

data.chText: 头几次横跨大西洋的商业飞行
data.enText: the first commercial flights across the Atlantic

data.chText: 赢利的；以获利为目的的
data.enText: making or intended to make a profit

data.chText: 这部电影票房收入不佳。
data.enText: The movie was not a commercial success (= did not make money) .

data.chText: 偏重利润和声望的；商业化的
data.enText: more concerned with profit and being popular than with quality

data.chText: 他们最近的音乐过分商业化了。
data.enText: Their more recent music is far too commercial.

data.chText: 由广告收入支付的；商业性的
data.enText: paid for by the money charged for broadcasting advertisements

data.chText: 商业电台 / 电视频道
data.enText: a commercial radio station/TV channel

data.chText: 商业化生产的 / 种植的 / 开发的
data.enText: commercially produced/grown/developed

data.chText: 这种产品还没有上市。
data.enText: The product is not yet commercially available.

data.chText: 他的发明从赢利角度看并不成功。
data.enText: His invention was not commercially successful.

data.chText: （电台或电视播放的）广告
data.enText: an advertisement on the radio or on television

data.text: ad ♦ advertisement ♦ commercial ♦ promotion ♦ advert ♦ trailer

data.chText: 以上各词均指广告、启事。
data.enText: These are all words for a notice, picture or film telling people about a product, job or service.
ad

data.chText: 指广告、启事：
data.enText: ( informal ) a notice, picture or film telling people about a product, job or service

data.chText: 我们在当地报纸上登了一则广告。
data.enText: We put an ad in the local paper.

data.chText: 新品种巧克力棒的广告
data.enText: an ad for a new chocolate bar

data.chText: 他在浏览报纸上的分类广告。
data.enText: He was scanning the classified ads (= the section in a newspaper with small advertisements arranged in groups according to their subject) .
advertisement

data.chText: 指广告、启事、广告样品、宣传的实例、广告活动或广告宣传：
data.enText: a notice, picture or film telling people about a product, job or service; an example of sth that shows its good qualities; the act of advertising sth and making it public

data.chText: 在当地报纸登一则广告来卖汽车。
data.enText: Put an advertisement in the local paper to sell your car.

data.chText: 肮脏的街道绝不是繁荣社会的景象。
data.enText: Dirty streets are no advertisement for a prosperous society.

data.chText: advertisement指广告时可简化为较非正式的ad或advert，指广告样品可简化为advert。
data.enText: When you are talking about a notice, picture or film telling people about a product, job or service, advertisement can be shortened to the more informal ad or ( BrE ) advert . When you are talking about an example of sth that shows its good qualities, advertisement can be shortened to advert .
commercial

data.chText: 指电视或电台播放的广告
data.enText: an advertisement on television or on the radio
promotion

data.chText: 指广告宣传、促销活动：
data.enText: a set of advertisements for a particular product or service; activities done in order to increase the sales of a product or service

data.chText: 当地产品的特别促销活动
data.enText: a special promotion of local products

data.chText: 她从事销售和推广工作。
data.enText: She works in sales and promotion.
advert

data.chText: 指广告、广告样品：
data.enText: ( BrE informal ) an advertisement

data.chText: 我从不看电视广告。
data.enText: I never watch the adverts on TV.
trailer

data.chText: 指电影或电视节目的预告片
data.enText: ( especially BrE ) a series of short scenes from a film/movie or television programme, shown in advance to advertise it
a(n) ad/advertisement/commercial/promotion/advert/trailer for sth
a TV/television/radio/cinema ad/advertisement/commercial/promotion/advert
a job ad/advertisement/advert
to run/show a(n) ad/advertisement/commercial/advert/trailer

data.chText: 以上各词尤用于企业或国家的经济活动或状况。
data.enText: These words all describe activities or situations that are connected with the use of money, especially by a business or country.
economic

data.chText: 指国家、地区或社会经济的、经济上的、经济学的：
data.enText: connected with the trade, industry and development of wealth of a country, an area or a society

data.chText: 这本书论及了那个时期的社会、经济和政治问题。
data.enText: This book deals with the social, economic and political issues of the period.
financial

data.chText: 指财政的、财务的、金融的：
data.enText: connected with money and finance

data.chText: 她陷入了财务困境。
data.enText: She had got into financial difficulties.

data.chText: 东京是主要的金融中心。
data.enText: Tokyo is a major financial centre.
commercial

data.chText: 指贸易的、商业的
data.enText: connected with the buying and selling of goods and services
monetary

data.chText: 指货币的、钱的，尤指一国的金融：
data.enText: ( formal or finance ) connected with money, especially all the money in a country

data.chText: 更为紧密的欧洲货币联盟
data.enText: closer European monetary union
budgetary

data.chText: 指财政预算的
data.enText: ( finance ) connected with a budget (= the money available or a plan of how it will be spent)
economic/financial/commercial/monetary/budgetary affairs/decisions/planning
the economic/financial/commercial/budgetary climate
the economic/financial/commercial/monetary side of sth
a(n) economic/financial/commercial centre

data.chText: 以上各词均指赚钱的、赢利的、有利可图的。
data.enText: These words all describe sb/sth that is making or is likely to make money.
successful

data.chText: 指赚钱的、成功的：
data.enText: making a lot of money, especially by being popular

data.chText: 那出剧在百老汇大获成功。
data.enText: The play was very successful on Broadway.

data.chText: 公司又度过了一个兴旺发达之年。
data.enText: The company has had another successful year.
profitable

data.chText: 指有利润的、赢利的：
data.enText: making a profit

data.chText: 一家赢利很高的企业
data.enText: a highly profitable business
commercial

data.chText: 指赢利的、以获利为目的的：
data.enText: [only before noun] making or intended to make a profit

data.chText: 这部电影票房收入不佳。
data.enText: The movie was not a commercial success (= made no profit) .
lucrative

data.chText: 指生意或工作赚大钱的、获利多的：
data.enText: (of business or work) producing or paying a large amount of money; making a large profit

data.chText: 他们在利润丰厚的海外市场上生意很多。
data.enText: They do a lot of business in lucrative overseas markets.
economic

data.chText: （常用于否定句中）指（工序、业务或活动）有利可图、可赚钱、合算：
data.enText: (often used in negative sentences) (of a process, business or activity) producing enough profit to continue

data.chText: 附近的一家超市开业后，当地的小商店就没有利润可赚了。
data.enText: Small local shops stop being economic when a supermarket opens up nearby.
to be/remain successful/profitable/lucrative/economic
to prove/seem/make sth/keep sth successful/profitable/lucrative/economic
a successful/profitable/lucrative business
a successful/profitable/lucrative year
a(n) commercial/economic success
highly/particularly/very successful/profitable/lucrative
fairly/quite successful/profitable/lucrative

simple_means.memory_skill: com 共同 + merc 商业，交易 + ial 属于…的 → 商业的

ex.chText: 他没有意识到自己的发现所具有的商业价值。
ex.enText: He failed to see the commercial value of his discovery.

ex.chText: 贵院是否教授商业函件写作?
ex.enText: Is commercial correspondence taught at your college?

synonyms.bx: 泛指与商品和服务的买卖有关的，通常作定语。

ex.chText: 如果你经商，应该遵守商法。
ex.enText: Obey the mercantile laws if you are engaged in business.

ex.chText: 中国一家新的商业征信所在纽约成立。
ex.enText: A new Chinese mercantile agency was established in New York.

synonyms.bx: 指与贸易和商业活动有关的，只作定语。

ex.chText: 墙上贴了一则招聘广告。
ex.enText: There is an advertisement on the wall which says:'Help Wanted.'

ex.chText: 报纸上广告实在太多了。
ex.enText: There are so many advertisements in the newspaper.

synonyms.bx: 非正式文体中可写作 ad，通常内容广泛、形式多样。

ex.chText: 你读过报纸上的那条广告了吗？
ex.enText: Have you read the advert/advertisement in the newspaper?
The advert/advertisement is to sell medicine.

ex.chText: 那个电视剧中插入的广告太多了，频频被打断。
ex.enText: The TV play was interrupted by too many commercials.

ex.chText: 好广告能让人们相信产品的亮点。
ex.enText: A good commercial convinces people of the attractive features of a product.

synonyms.bx: 专指电视台或电台播放的产品宣传广告。

tr: a commercially sponsored ad on radio or television
connected with or engaged in or sponsored by or used in commerce or commercial enterprises
of the kind or quality used in commerce

value.def: Commercial means involving or relating to the buying and selling of goods.

example.ex: Docklands in its heyday was a major centre of industrial and commercial activity...
example.tran: 港区在其最繁荣的时期曾是主要的工商业活动中心。

example.ex: Attacks were reported on police, vehicles and commercial premises.
example.tran: 据报道，警察、车辆和商业经营场所均遭到袭击。

value.def: Commercial organizations and activities are concerned with making money or profits, rather than, for example, with scientific research or providing a public service.

example.ex: British Rail has indeed become more commercial over the past decade...
example.tran: 过去10年来，英国铁路确实变得更加商业化了。

example.ex: Conservationists in Chile are concerned over the effect of commercial exploitation of forests...
example.tran: 对森林的商业开发所带来的影响让智利的自然资源保护者们感到忧心忡忡。

example.ex: Whether the project will be a commercial success is still uncertain.
example.tran: 这个项目是否赚钱还是个未知数。

value.tran: (组织、活动)营利的，商业化的，偏重利润的

example.ex: British Aerospace reckon that the plane will be commercially viable if 400 can be sold...
example.tran: 英国航空航天公司估计这个型号的飞机如果能卖出400架，就可实现盈利。

example.ex: Insulin is produced commercially from animals...
example.tran: 为获利从动物体内提取胰岛素。

example.ex: Designers are becoming more commercially minded.
example.tran: 设计者们变得更有商业意识。

value.def: A commercial product is made to be sold to the public.

example.ex: They are the leading manufacturer in both defence and commercial products.
example.tran: 在军工产品和民用产品的制造方面，他们都处于领先地位。

value.tran: (产品)商品化的，供市场出售的

example.ex: It was the first commercially available machine to employ artificial intelligence.
example.tran: 这是第一台作为商品出售的采用人工智能技术的机器。

value.def: A commercial vehicle is a vehicle used for carrying goods, or passengers who pay.

example.ex: Commercial vehicles, coaches and lorries are required by law to be fitted with tachographs.
example.tran: 法律规定商用车辆、长途汽车和卡车要安装转速计。

example.ex: ...the fastest crossing of the Atlantic by a commercial passenger vessel.
example.tran: 商用客船最快的一次横渡大西洋

value.def: Commercial television and radio are paid for by the broadcasting of advertisements, rather than by the government.

example.ex: ...Classic FM, the first national commercial radio station.
example.tran: 国内首家商业广播电台——经典调频

value.tran: (电视、广播)靠广告收入维持的，商业性的

value.def: Commercial is used to describe something such as a film or a type of music that it is intended to be popular with the public, and is not very original or of high quality.

example.ex: There's a feeling among a lot of people that music has become too commercial.
example.tran: 很多人都觉得音乐变得过于商业化了。

value.tran: (电影或音乐)商业化的，迎合大众口味的

value.def: A commercial is an advertisement that is broadcast on television or radio.

example.ex: The government has launched a campaign of television commercials and leaflets.
example.tran: 政府通过电视广告和传单的形式发起了宣传活动。

partsOfSpeech.dec: com 共同 + merc 商业，交易 + e → 双方进行交易 → 商业
com 共同 + merc 商业，交易 + ial 属于…的 → 商业的
merc 商业，交易 + ant …的，具有…性质的 + ile 属于…的 → 贸易的；商人的
merch 商业，交易 + and + ise 使 → 用来交易的东西 → 商品
merch 商业，交易 + ant 表人 → 商人

rootsaffixes.indicate: 表形容词，“具有…的，属于…的”
rootsaffixes.title: -ial

partsOfSpeech.dec: bene 好 + fic 使…的，产生…的，具有某种性质的 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 有益的
commerce 商业 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 商业的
confident 确信的 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 秘密的
con 共同 + gen 产生 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 产生共同点 → 意气相投的
face 面孔 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 面孔的；面部用的
im 不 + part 部分 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 不偏向任何一部分 → 公平的
judic 法律 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 法庭的
president 总统，校长 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 总统（职位）的
province 省 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 偏狭的；地方性的
